<!--
  README.md — MyClaude Product Showcase Template v3.0.0
  =====================================================

  This is NOT a template with variables. This is a BLUEPRINT.
  /create scaffolds from this structure. /fill populates with real content.
  /package strips WHY comments and injects badges at the bottom.
  The final README goes to Firestore as raw markdown (50K max) and renders
  on myclaude.sh/p/{slug} as the product page.

  THE PHILOSOPHY:
  Everything above the install command is MARKETING — sell the product.
  Everything below the install command is DOCUMENTATION — support the user.
  The README is a landing page with a terminal at the bottom.

  STRUCTURE (in order — each section earns the reader's next scroll):
  1. HERO: Problem hook + one-line solution (5 seconds to decide)
  2. PROOF: Output example, before/after, or visual demo
  3. INSTALL: One command. Copy-paste. Done.
  4. IS THIS FOR ME?: Qualifier — who benefits, who doesn't
  5. QUICK START: 3 steps or less to first value
  6. FEATURES: What it does — each feature with enough depth to understand
  7. USE CASES: Real scenarios — "when you're doing X, use Y"
  8. HOW IT WORKS: The method behind the magic (earns trust)
  9. TYPE-SPECIFIC: Usage/Architecture/Events per product type
  10. REQUIREMENTS: What you need
  11. COMPATIBILITY: Where it works
  12. LANGUAGE: Locale-adaptive statement
  13. LICENSE + FOOTER: Metadata, badges, author

  TRILINGUAL:
  Primary language section first (full product showcase).
  Second and third languages follow with the SAME depth and richness.
  Language navigation bar at the top with anchor links.
  /fill generates translations from the primary language content.

  VOICE:
  Professional but warm. Direct but not cold. Confident but not arrogant.
  Show personality — myClaude products have character.
  Write for someone scanning 20 products at 11pm deciding which to install.
-->

